Pulmonary edema: most likely caused by ischemia
Rest angina with dynamic ST changes ≥ 0.5 mm
New or worsening rales, S3, or MR murmur
Hypotension, bradycardia, tachycardia
Bundle branch block, new or presumed new
Sustained ventricular tachycardia
Positive serum cardiac biomarkers

Intermediate risk
No high-risk feature but must have one of the following:
Prior MI, peripheral or cerebrovascular disease
Prolonged rest pain (> 20 min) that resolves
Rest angina (> 20 min or relieved with rest or sublingual NTG)
Nocturnal angina
New-onset, severe angina within 2 wk with moderate or high likelihood of CAD
T-wave changes
